message: Focus on soft ingredients. The optimal strategy is to use scissors to cut one natural soft item and one artificial soft item. Then, combine these two cut items to create a high-value blend (typically 80 points). Finally, use the frame on this blended item to reach the maximum score of 100 points. message: The key to 100 points is combining a 'natural, soft, cut' item with an 'artificial, soft, cut' item, and then framing it. First, use 'scissors' on a natural soft ingredient (like a flower or leaf) and an artificial soft ingredient (like paper or sponge). This will give you two 'cut' items. Then, combine these two different 'cut soft' items. This combined item will be worth 80 points. Finally, use the 'frame' tool on this combined item, which will increase its value to 100 points. Ignore hard items for this strategy, as they don't seem to combine for high values or benefit from framing.
